- 1.0.3 | Mar 02 2026:
[Fix] Add standard copyright headers to test suite files — Makefile,
      Dockerfile, and all five .bats files now carry rfxn copyright and
      GPL v2 license header (F-050)
[New] 19 new self-tests for batsman_build(), batsman_clean(), and
      batsman_run() routing — validates Dockerfile resolution, image
      tagging, build error paths, three cleanup modes, variant mapping
      in clean, and execution mode dispatch via docker stub pattern
      (F-020, F-021, F-047)
[New] 7 new self-tests for install-bats.sh — validates SHA256 mismatch
      detection, TLS fallback mode routing (modes 0/1/2), unknown
      TLS_FALLBACK error, default version values, and complete three-
      library install flow via mock command pattern (F-024)
[New] install-bats.sh: SHA256 checksum verification for all three pinned
      tarballs (bats-core, bats-support, bats-assert) — download integrity
      backstop compensating for disabled TLS verification on legacy OS
[New] README: migration guide section with version-specific upgrade notes
      for consumers — covers BATS 1.13.0 run-variable unset breaking change,
      SHA256 checksum verification, parallelism changes, CLI strictness
[Change] Demote default parallelism from nproc*2 to nproc for both intra-OS
      container count (run-tests-core.sh) and cross-OS job count
      (Makefile.tests PARALLEL_JOBS) — prevents compounding (nproc*2)²
      container storms on test-all-parallel targets
[Fix] CLI flags requiring a value (--os, --filter, --filter-tags, --formatter,
      --timeout, --report-dir) now error on missing trailing argument instead
      of consuming the next flag or setting an empty value
[Fix] batsman_run() now checks batsman_parse_args and batsman_build return
      codes — parse or build failures propagate immediately instead of
      continuing with undefined state
[Fix] --timeout validates that value is a positive integer — rejects
      non-numeric input from both CLI and BATSMAN_TEST_TIMEOUT env var
[Change] Unknown --flags now emit a warning and pass through to bats without
      setting explicit_files — previously they silently routed to direct mode
[New] End-of-options (--) support in argument parser — all arguments after --
      are treated as file operands regardless of prefix
[New] 20 new self-tests for CLI argument parsing hardening (93 total)
[Fix] install-bats.sh: add set -o pipefail — download failures in pipe to tar
      are no longer masked by tar's exit code
[Fix] install-bats.sh: refactor fetch_tarball() from stdout pipe to file-based
      download — prevents partial-data corruption when TLS fallback retries
      after primary downloader writes partial output
[Fix] install-bats.sh: add network timeouts (wget --timeout=60, curl
      --connect-timeout 30 --max-time 120) — hung connections no longer stall
      Docker builds indefinitely
[Fix] README: correct container naming pattern from <project>-test-<os>-<slot>
      to <project>-<os>-<pid>-g<N> matching actual code
[Change] Extract variant-mapping loop from batsman_build() and batsman_clean()
      into standalone _batsman_resolve_base_os() function — eliminates three
      copies of identical logic (two production, one test)
[Fix] Variant mapping tests now call production _batsman_resolve_base_os()
      instead of test-local reimplementation (F-022)
[Fix] Remove duplicate "all 9 base Dockerfiles exist" test from
      01-version.bats — canonical copy retained in 03-validation.bats (F-048)
[Fix] Version test extracts BATSMAN_VERSION from source file via grep instead
      of hardcoding — eliminates manual test update on version bumps (F-049)
[Fix] --help and --version now return instead of exit in sourced library —
      prevents process termination when called from sourced context; adds
      _batsman_done flag checked by batsman_run() for clean short-circuit (F-019)
[Fix] Add nproc fallback chain (nproc || sysctl -n hw.logicalcpu || echo 1)
      in run-tests-core.sh and Makefile.tests — enables macOS host support
      where GNU nproc is unavailable (F-011)
[Fix] self-test.yml: widen push branch pattern from '1.*' to '[0-9]*.*' —
      CI triggers on any version branch, not just 1.x (F-027)
[Fix] Makefile.tests parallel xargs targets: wrap commands with sh -c to
      emit per-OS failure banners to stderr — xargs -P exit 123 no longer
      hides which OS targets failed (F-032)
[Fix] Makefile.tests clean-all regex: add hyphen to character class so
      hyphenated project names (e.g., my-project) are matched for image
      cleanup (F-010)
[New] 12 new self-tests for execution mode functions (batsman_run_direct,
      batsman_run_sequential, batsman_run_parallel) — validates Docker command
      construction, timeout/report handling, container naming, TAP counting,
      and error propagation via docker stub pattern (F-026)
[New] 2 new self-tests validating _batsman_done flag behavior for --help and
      --version direct-call safety (107 total)
[Fix] Help text: document --parallel forces tap formatter (F-016); add -h
      short flag (F-044); document --parallel 0 = auto-detect (F-045); add
      CLI overrides env var precedence for --timeout and --report-dir (F-046)
[Fix] README: fix TLS fallback description to reflect OS-specific ordering
      instead of describing only mode 2 (F-031); add PARALLEL_JOBS to
      Makefile.tests config reference (F-017); add formatter restriction
      note to Parallel Test Orchestration section (F-016); add CLI > env var
      precedence notes for BATSMAN_TEST_TIMEOUT and BATSMAN_REPORT_DIR (F-046)
[Fix] CHANGELOG: clarify BATS Bash floor 3.2+ vs batsman requirement of
      4.1+/CentOS 6 to avoid misreading project minimum (F-042)
